page1.title: About Me
page1.content: A PhD student doing research on the stability of renewable energy patterns throughout time. I am also a lecture lead / Mentor in Schulich Ignite 1. In my free time, I contribute to open source projects such as STUMPY2. I am a never-stop-learning person :) . Schulich Ignite is a club with a mission to inspire the next generation of programmers. ↩ . | STUMPY is a powerful and scalable Python library for modern time series analysis ↩ . |
